dS=\sqrt{ 1+\left(\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}\right)^2 + \left(\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}\right)^2 }dxdy
x^2+y^2+z^2=r^2
dS=\frac{r}{z}dxdy
dxdy=r^2\sin(\theta)d\theta d\phi
z=r\cos(\theta)
dS=r^2 \tan(\theta) d\theta d\phi
\theta
\pi/2
dxdy=dx\times dy =r^2\begin{vmatrix} \hat r&\hat\theta&\hat\phi\\ 0&\cos\theta\cos\phi\, d\theta&-\sin\theta\sin\phi\, d\phi\\ 0&\cos\theta\cos\phi\, d\theta&\sin\theta\cos\phi\, d\phi \end{vmatrix}=r^2\sin\theta\cos\theta\,d\theta\, d\phi.
